# A complex field - one that simpleFieldChain rejects, e.g. because
# its value is on its own line, has a doc comment, or sits in a
# non-collapsible chain - flushes the alignment table at the
# construction stage, just like a non-field decl. Simple fields
# above and below the complex field form independent alignment
# groups and do not pad to a shared key column.
#
# In the norelpos case the value's Newline RelPos is gone, so
# `deep` becomes a simple field; the file is then in a Group
# (programmatic-source path) and the whole struct fits flat at
# width 80, so it renders as a single comma-separated line with
# no padding involved.
-- in.cue --
foo: 1
longname: 22
deep:
	9
bar: 333
bazinga: 4444
-- out/relpos --
foo:      1
longname: 22
deep:
	9
bar:     333
bazinga: 4444
-- out/norelpos --
foo: 1, longname: 22, deep: 9, bar: 333, bazinga: 4444
